caption: Good food, good sides, good service! Also, the streetery is right there so you can order takeout from here and eat at tables on the street. There are tents up now, also you can BYOB and BYOD (bring your own bottle / dog)

Pretty decent barbeque place. One or two really nice options, like their deviled eggs and smoked salmon tacos.  They could make their "spicy sauce" a little spicier and add a little flavor to their brisket.
This place never fails to impress. They serve excellent dishes for affordable pricing, there are no long waits even when the place is packed.

Great service from the staff and the best hot dogs around downtown Bethesda their burgers are good too check them out of you around Bethesda. Their online ordering system is easy too and you earn rewards point for each visit 😋😋
Fantastic BBQ, pork, brisket and chicken. Really good bbq.

Got a half rack of ribs today with the spicy BBQ seasoning. They were delicious and juicy. Some reviews here mentioned they were dry but mine were perfect. Very tasty! Will definitely order from here again. The restaurant is very nicely laid out for takeout order pickup too.

Wow.   This reminds me of someone with a new smoker and discount meat.   The ribs are LITERALLY composed of fat.  More fat than meat and bone combined!!!!    We had to give an entire rack to the dogs.   The cole slaw was completely dry.   The brisket was tough and spicy.   I just can’t say how disappointing this was.
Great customer service and great food! I love their sausage the most. It is perfectly smoked. Also, they use local artist's work to decorate the restaurant. It's pretty unique.

I frequent this outstanding place often since I enjoy the good air that is characterizes this restaurant. The staff is extraordianrillyremarkably welcoming and qualified. The service is remarkablywonderfully rapid. Not to mention, the food you eat is highly distinguished. I ate there more than once and I was always delighted. The rate is fair. I highly recommend this restaurant to my friends and family.
Good food and curbside service.
This spot sure knows how to satisfy their clients. Always with a welcoming approach. The food is fairly priced, constantly tasty and neat.
First and last time going. Got the chicken platter with extremely dry chicken and cornbread that had no flavor and was so dry I couldn’t eat it. Side of Mac and cheese was decent but not worth it.

Pretty disappointed. Food is dry and lacking flavor. Got the brisket platter which contains very thinly sliced and dry meat. The cornbread had no flavor and crumbled the second you picked it up. Cole slaw had a weird aftertaste like it had been sitting for a while. Only redeeming quality was the BBQ sauce it came with and the baked beans, but even those weren’t outstanding. Google has this listed at 4.2 but Apple has it pegged around 3.5 which is probably where it should be.

Got the pulled pork and brisket combos. Pulled pork was tolerable, brisket was pretty much beef jerky with a thin layer of dried out sauce. Cornbread was terrible, mac and cheese was processed and plastic like.  Everything was cold. Coleslaw was decent.

I just ordered food from here and it was not good. The food looked and tasted like it had been sitting out since the previous day. The burger was was over cooked and the ribs were really dry and so was the corn bread. That was a waste of $50+ for the things I ordered.SMH 🤬😡 very disappointed!
Definitely not as amazing as I expected it to be based on the menu, but it was okay.
As good bbq as you're going to get in Bethesda. Wouldn't hold up in Texas, but all things considered the food is pretty tasty and the covid pick up is solid. I will certainly buy food here again.

I celebrated my birthday today in this excellent restaurant. Well we had a brilliant evening and the venue was indeed the reason for this strong gathering. The waiters  contributed in a sweet way, the meals were very good and my buddies were very  overjoyed. We shall definitely come back again for more joyful events. thanks very much.

Wanted to like this place more! The ribs and brisket were very dry. I hope this was just an off night for restaurant, this was the first time we had it. The sides were good, we got the scalloped potatoes and Mac and cheese. However, the cucumber salad just tasted like vinegar.
Good bbq for Maryland and good service. FYI there is no dine-in, only pick up
I always stop purchasing some food in here. I enjoyed the quick customer service and well cooked dishes. Keep up the good work.

It is insane how much money me, a broke person who is supposed to be saving for grad school, has spent here. I will sound so basic, but I LOVE their potato salad. I order it every single time and I get the large and I eat it on its own, as an entree. It is delicious! Oh, their onion rings are the bomb! Dip it in the spicy bbq sauce and your eyes might roll into the back of your head from the joy you will feel. This is definitely a place you need to be trying.

I consider the measure of a BBQ place to be their brisket and ribs. I've had both here, and although the ribs were good, the brisket was dry, too thin cut, and not very smoky at all. Hence, I only give 3 stars (2 for brisket, 4 for ribs). Their spicy BBQ sauce is really good though and made the brisket edible. Their smoked lamb, potato, corn bread, and cole slaw were good.

Yesterday, I ordered a half rack dry with an order of smoked turkey and a pork chipotle wrap...the ribs were tender and juicy...best I've ever had. Highly recommended, a great small business in Bethesda.

We love eating out. Yesterday we arrived in this delicious place which friends told us about. We passed a delightful evening there with delicious dishes and  an experienced crew and  a professional cook. We  added this restaurant in our phone list  and we shall certainly go again soon. We highly recommend.
Not impressed,  overpriced, brisket and chicken both dry.  French fries and corn bread were good.  Don't waste your time or money!
I'm from North Carolina. I was not expecting good bbq, but I was still exceptionally disappointed. The atmosphere is a stereotype.

This restaurant is definitely one of the most attractive place to eat in the neighborhood. Whenever I come there I am awfully satisfied. They manage their very high  level service and the highest level of dishes  they give. You no doubt will love this place. Warmly  recommended.
French fries were good.

Wow. This is terrible barbecue. I’m pretty sure they make the brisket with steakums. The sauce has no life. Overall the worst most overpriced bbq I’ve ever had that doesn’t resemble any regional style of bbq at all. A complete waste of money. I tried the 3 meat combo with ribs, pork, and brisket and threw the whole platter in the garbage after tasting each meat.

This restaurant is clearly one of the coolest place in the neighborhood. Whenever I go there I am greatly pleased. They manage their very high  standard service and the highest level of dishes  they serve. You no doubt will love this place. Highly  recommended.
I just enjoy their food. I always get great customer service there. The place is well organised and the employees are always kind. Would recommend to others.

Friendly staff, I was happy and surprised I could get in on friday night with no wait but there was nobody there at 8:30 on a friday night so made me wonder a  little. So I try BBQ places everywhere I go and I thought the portion size for price was a little small but... My real complaint was that I could barely taste any "smoke" flavor. Minimal on the pulled pork and nearly non- existent on the chicken ( pulled) which was too dry, as was the cornbread. I really like a stronger smoke flavor but if you don't, it might be worth a try.
Awesome food
Great local barbecue spot. Terrific service. Highly recommend the ribs!

This is a great little dive BBQ shop. Their food is cheaper than most BBQ joints of this caliber, and they're in the middle of Bethesda!! Must do a lot of volume; people are constantly popping in to pick up carry out. Great beer selection, too. And... THEY DELIVER BEER with food. 😮 VERY happy I found this place! 🤘

If you're from the south don't come here.  My wife and I are from the south (NC) and I have to say this was by far the worst bbq I have ever had. We walked in and were rather insulted by the "southern culture" on display. It was so bad, and I in such disbelief, that I asked the bartender if the owners were southern. They are, in fact, from Bethesda. Which made sense, as my wife and I thought the restaurant was set up like a northerner's vision of the south.  The service was fine, it was friendly and accommodating. My wife and I just found ourselves rather insulted by restaurant a complete parody of the south. The food itself was bad, and not priced well. I had more of a hope for the quality, but was unfortunately proven right.  Before the complaints, everyone knows NOVA and Maryland is the north.
AMAZINGLY, DELICIOUS BBQ!! EXTREMELY FRIENDLY STAFF! GREAT ATMOSPHERE FOR FRIENDS AND FAMILY!! HIGHLY RECOMMEND!
Good food

We arrived at this spot for dinner. This restaurant was recommended to us by a friend.  Well, it was very nice. we were warmly welcomed by the crew  and we had an excellent feeling. The meal was great. We enjoyed every moment and we will definitely return to this restaurant. We recommend this place to all.
Absolutely a spot worth stopping over, the food is good and well prepared, the cost is fair and it is consistently well kept here. Keep it up.
I absolutely enjoyed their dishes and service, fantastic area very close to my house. The staff members are always friendly. Will come visit again.
Smoked wings, Yes! Chicken soup, No!
Wings are super good
Excellent spot to grab food when in a rush. The customer service is quick, pricing is affordable, awesome atmosphere. I highly recommend this spot.
Friendly  good food. Enjoyed the visit and meal.
Good atmosphere and awesome bartenders make this place a pretty chillax spot. Play with the wooden owl while youre in there
Great BBQ! Friendly service and good specials.

I visit this lovely spot many times a year! This is the best place to dine.  I go there routinely. The cooking is of high quality, the staff members are helpful and the charge is reasonable. I like eating in this place for a rich meal.
Exceptional and delightful food, I love the mood this spot has, and the employees were super nice. Will definitely come back in the future.
I really enjoyed both the food and the ambience.
Food are they kidding, try harder and maybe you can call it food. Till then even McDonald's is a better choice.
Best BBQ and vibe in dc

This is such a great place to get food! Such nice people that work here and the food came so quickly as well. I definitely will come here again and recommend it for anyone in the area. I ordered the pulled spicy BBQ chicken on a Kaiser bun with fries on the side. Thank you so much for a wonderful experience! 😊
Great food and service. Hands down best BBQ in South Florida !

I was surprised I have ordered food here for my office before but I will never again. Food was not good, ribs and brisket were soso; overpriced for the portion sizes. Exchanged my side of what was supposed to be bbq beans for extremely salty scallop potatoes. I would never order again.
Good bbq

Great spot. I'm always happy I stopped in. Smoke has a welcoming, local bar feel. Food is good (don't expect KC, TX, etc BBQ - this is MD), comes out quickly, and is reasonably priced. The beer selection is hard to beat in Bethesda. Staff and regulars are both friendly.
Pub Grub. Nuff Said.
Great food and great service. Friendly bartender. Will definitely go again.
The BBQ bowl was great!! Pulled pork with spicy sauce  corn, tomatoes, cucumbers, onions and tortilla strips. Yum!!
Everything on the menu is fantastic.
Amazing $4 happy hour with half price wings every Monday.
Awesome Arnold Palmers, collared greens, and smoked meats.

Dry cornbread. Flavorless mac n cheese. Their brisket has no right to be called brisket...it's more like thinly sliced smoked Gyro. Not worth the inflated price. Come for the drinks. Leave the food alone.
Spent $20 on BBQ and a Soda today. Ridiculously overpriced. Awful food. Couldn't even eat the coleslaw. Dry cornbread. BBQ had no flavor to it. How do you mess up potatoes?!?
Great food, good drinks and a friendly staff. I'll definitely will check out again.
Excellent service and location
Ok BBQ. Not amazing but tasty. Skip the deviled eggs. They were too salty. Decor and outdoor seating were nice but people were smoking in the eating area. Turn off.
Relaxed cozy atmosphere.  Great ribs.  Modest selection of beer on tap.  I'll be going back soon.
The food was decent but I think it might have been better if it was hot
Very casual "Townie" place with the best BBQ and smokehouse food in the area.  Great prices too!  Keep going back for the great food and good beer selection.
Sauce way to sweet. Wings were just a bit over smoked.
worst brisket I have ever had. tasted like rubber. comparable to arby's brisket. i was not able to finish it.
Decent food. Good conversation. Have visited multiple times.

The food and drinks are great. The friendly hospitable service here is even better. I like to come in when Michelle is working at the bar she is a total sweetheart that knows how to make all the customers feel at home welcomed.
Great food... Bonus... Dart boards
Excellent food and service!

I want to love it but I don't. The bbq is a hair above average. It doesn't feel to me like its break your foot off in it smoked BBQ. However, I couldn't point you to better and I've looked miles in every direction.  That being said, the staff is beyond awesome. The customers are loyal and regular. And the specials... The specials have me ordering something most weeks.
Great bbq and sauces- quaint place to eat and chat and have a martini.
Great food.my go to place
Great food at a great price.
Didn't have a good experience there
Best place for Smoke BBQ in Bethesda.  Locally owned and operated as well!
I ordered food from here on uber eats. The only disappointment I had was that I wasn’t there to shake the hand of the man that cooked this beautiful meat.

Totally stumbled across this place while driving around and I'm glad I did!  Had ribs, smoked sausage, pulled pork, collard greens, beans, slaw, and cornbread. Everything, even the slaw, was delicious. Good spicy BBQ sauce and they even have a vinegar sauce.  On top of that, it has a full bar, tons of beers, and happy hour.
Good food. Good prices. Good music. Good people.
The brisket tasted like rubber. Horrible.
Nice
Food was pretty good. The cornbread could use more butter and honey. It was a bit dry. Their BBQ sauces are delicious.It's a relaxing atmosphere and the place is very clean.

This was always one of the restaurants we walked past, but always wanted to try. I can’t believe it took us so long because the food was delicious and they also have a great craft beer selection. It’s also usually quiet and the service is great. We will for sure be going back soon.
If you like your meat dry and fries extra salty and no taste at all, this your place. Beers are fine and serving is good. The stars are for them.
Delicious food
Love the food and the drinks never disappoint. The smoked ice bourbon is great and the smoked chicken wings are worth a try.

We walked into a nicely decorated barbecue place on Cordell Avenue in Bethesda- first time never even heard of it before and apparently it's been there 5 years. I like barbecue I like reasonably priced delicious barbecue. This could be the place near home, how did I miss hearing about this place thank goodness for Google. We had a complete meal and everything was really good I recommend going here for dinner on one of those days when you really want barbecue or if you can't decide what to eat try this place. I'm told they deliver. 2. Here's my in-depth review we really enjoyed our meal and I'll try to attach the pictures The onion rings were cooked perfectly, when you bite through it you bite through it including the onion. Oh by the way they taste really good too. Pulled pork was was so good that I almost couldn't stop eating my pork sandwiches to take a drink. I literally had to think about putting my sandwich down to get a drink and stop myself from just consuming this terrific barbecue sandwich. At this point I also had a chance to try the side of slaw that comes with everything I'm told. Different and tasty and certainly the chef's owned seasonings in this slaw. The sandwich was so good I had to try the ribs. Oh my God so meaty maybe the meatiest I've had. Very nice house flavor barbecue sauce tops the ribs. They're also bottles of the sweeter sauce and hot sauce that you choose between when you order your ribs. I got the scalloped potatoes as my side. A mistake, I personally do not consider really nice mashed potatoes with cheese melted across the top of them in their bowl scalloped potatoes. They were mashed potatoes with skins with cheese on top. My dining partner wisely chose the waffle sweet potatoe fries. They stayed hot at the plate unlike usual sweet potato fries. These waffle sweet potato fries State hot the entire time they were cooked really well and that have wonderfully fresh taste to them
Food didn't even taste like it had been smoked at all.

In town for business and found this place randomly. Great smoked brisket sandwich and fries! The lady at the counter was friendly and welcoming. Had a decent craft brew selection as well which is always a bonus. Definitely make this a stop on your visit to town!
The BEST place for BBQ in Bethesda, probably in the whole DC metro area. Their BBQ bowls are delicious and Jim always knows what to get you for a drink.
Quick, delicious BBQ.
Deserves 10 stars

For a restaurant called smoke, I expected their pulled pork to have decent smoked flavor.  Instead the pulled pork lacked any significant flavor, there was no real bark on the meat, the bbq sauce was generic-bland and (because I ordered it on Uber, so admittedly not their fault) the mac and cheese was lukewarm.    The cornbread wasn't bad, but it didn't really impress either.
Dank brisket and drinks. Unpretentious atmosphere

Reasonable prices, exceptional service, delicious food, and the beer - we're going back for the beer. 🍺 The recommendations for both food and beverage options by the staff were spot-on. They helped us choose the perfect pint and recommended sides that were particularly tasty. Samples the ribs, pork, turkey, cornbread, baked beans, and scalloped potatoes. Next time I want a full rack of ribs and I'm not sharing. Great place to get food AND BEER to go. WiFi is available, kid friendly, power outlets available. I would study here if I wouldn't become drunk, fat, and happy.
Great tasting food but a little expensive.
Very good pulled pork and  Mac & cheese. The atmosphere is laid back and the staff is very friendly. Been there 4 times already and will keep going back.
Nothing to complain or boast about, it was just alright.
A casual setting as BBQ should be!  Great BBQ and good drinks/service!
Awesome food and atmosphere.

I met my son here for lunch and it wasn't much to look at but the aromas and friendly staff and patrons made it a keeper. They have a smoker on the premises which was producing the good smells. We had the pulled port and the brisket sandwiches. Delicious! They made their on sauces on the table in a basket. There was a bar with tap, bottled beer and spirits.
Excellent ribs and great happy hour deals!

Their BBQ sauce uses Worcester sause so contains fish.    That ment I had to order something without sause.   Fortunately the brisket was available with out sause.   Unfortunately it wasn't very tasty.

Very nice staff, BUT I  don't think I've ever been more ripped off for an expensive meal than this.  Went a long way to pick up. The lamb platter contained just enough to cover my open palm.  The 20 dollar half rack, while tasty according to my guest, was shockingly small.  My pulled pork bbq  sandwich  was similarly inadequate for the price, but worse was that it was a gooey composite of who knows what.  The mac and cheese side used the new Kraft tasteless cheddar.  My order for large fries was not even in the bag.  The corn bread was 1 square inch.  Crowning this was the cole slaw serving for the $20 rack was in a tiny plastic cup that held exactly on tablespoon.  Some things are just wrong!
Wings n ribs r top notch
I called in with my two young children to pick up a take away. Service was quick and the food was delicious. Top marks. I'll be back.
Love the ribs!

Get the Fried Green Tomato BLT when you can because it sells out fast! Been here so many times and I finally just ate one. It was the BOMB! The bartenders make amazing infusion too which the mixtures are homemade, I believe. They also have great draft beer on tap.
Menu, can't miss, staff rocks, play Orioles/ Redskins games
Best coleslaw I've had in memory.
Delicious, great staff and crowd. Food and beer list is great.
The aroma pulled me in..... The choices had mmy mouth watering..... The service was friendly. THE FOOD WAS GOOD! THE PRICE WAS NICE! 👍👍👍
Great food
Great food, at first the prices seemed high but you definitely get your money's worth. One of the best BBQ's in the area!
It's lit
Get off your duff and get some good BBQ. Head to Smoke and get your grub on. The food is on point. Menu is good. Atmosphere is fantastic.
Awesome bbq place! Delicious 😋
Good pulled pork on Mac and cheese.  Very well cooked pork and creamy Mac & cheese

Pretty much go to Smoke BBQ for the mash potato bowl at least once a week it seems. Also use them for catering once a month for the office and they always deliver a good meal with the pulled pork sandwiches. Jim is easy going, funny, and attentive which is a tough combination to pull off in the food and beverage industry!

This bbq joint is ducked off...its a hidden gem. The BEST bbq I had in a long time and I'm from Texas. Don't forget to try the cornbread you won't regret it! By the way...Shoutout to the staff...great customer service.

Solid food here, I've tried a decent amount of their menu so far everything has been good. Service is great they're very friendly. Great spot if you need a quick bite or you can belly up to the bar and enjoy your BBQ with some beer and bourbon, or sweet tea for you younger readers.
Came on poker night. Still great service.

Fantastic food, even better beer. Smoker in the back is constantly cranking so the food is fresh and delicious. Sauce is wonderful. The thing I would recommend the most though? A nice bourbon or rye over their smoked ice. Perfect addition to any meal had here.
Friendly staff, great ribs. It's quickly become a regular spot for me.
great back ribs
My pulled pork wasn't tender, but everybody else loved this place

I got down on a sliced brisket plate and thoroughly enjoyed it.  Just came from TX and haven't tried BBQ here yet, but the meat was moist, and the sides/sauces had the right amount of flavor and kick.  Atmosphere felt like Austin, the people were welcoming and the service was on point.  I will come here again.
Good BBQ. I heard that the ribs are great. I had the chili which was a good chili.
This is the BBQ you can get in Bethesda.
Great food and great service
Meat was very good,  the sides not so good, chili more like stew. Good service.
The food was absolutely amazing! BBQ is my favorite kind of food and this place is true to BBQ. They even offer the proper side dishes like collards. Portion was very large.

Bland chicken with no smokey flavor. The brisket was dry but also looked and tasted like the frozen cheesesteak meat you would buy at the grocery store. The mac and cheese was flavorless. Portion sizes were also fairly small. The sauce was average, but they gave us a laughably small amount for takeout. I would choose any other BBQ place than returning here.
The BBQ platters and sides definitely hit the spot.
Got carryout from here and it was pretty good. Next time I will try it in the restaurant.
Ordered the ribs and they were fantastic!  I would definitely come again.
Just had it for the first time, I will definitely come back!
Perfect food, perfect portions, perfect price.  Atmosphere was great.  Not a lot of seating for larger parties.  Perfect for just me, though!

Look, I don't enjoy ripping restaurants apart on the web. But the food here is just plain bad. While I know not to expect really great BBQ from a joint in Bethesda MD, or most anywhere in DC for that matter, near everything here was either overcooked or tasteless. The brisket was just insultingly bad. It was chewy, over salted, over cooked, and reminded me of something I might get from the lunch ladies in grade school. The ribs had no smoke flavor, with absolutely no smoke ring and were dry and overcooked, with a typical bbq sauce smother job to cover the lazy cooking. The service was great and the place had a cool vibe, but I just cant get over how bad the meats were. Just terrible.

First and only time here, so far.Will definitely come back and will add this place to my list of good places to eat! The service was excellent and the staff were very personable. I thought the ribs were really good. Pulled pork sandwich was standard, but good. North Carolina vinegar sauce was good. Collards were spiced up and very good! Fried pickles were also very good, as was the accompanying horseradish sauce. Scalloped potatoes looked really good, but over-spiced with something, maybe thyme? Didn't really like the dish because of this. "Smoke" was there in the food, for me at just the right amount - the 'smoke" did not overwhelm the food like some other places do. You can tell the difference between beef & chicken, and not just a generic smoked meat taste.
The meat had no taste, and the sides were underwhelming. The cost of the meal was too much for bland food.
Really kind staff and great barbecue!!
Pulled pork was okay but it was a very small portion. Only went once though
Favorite place to go.  Great staff, BBQ and whiskey selection, as well as stellar comedy and live music on the weekends.

If you're in Bethesda and want BBQ this is the place to go. The pulled pork platter or the sandwich is a safe pick. The mac--n-cheese and BBQ beans are grrat sides. Cornbread is a bit dry and I'm not sure what they're trying to do with their coleslaw. I like my coleslaw a bit sweet and this is just not good.

I ordered a spinach salad with salmon. It tasted and smelled like rubber. The salmon was so over cook and rubbery I couldn't pick it up with a fork. I had to use my fingers to break a piece apart and it literally bent in my hand instead of flaking like salmon should. I couldn't eat it. I had to tie it in a bag because the rubber smell was so strong. At least they have decent sauce. Wont be ordering here again.
Great pulled pork sandwiches, they even delivered to NIH campus. Would recommend.
Friendly neighborhood bbq joint.

Where's the smoke?   The ribs and the pulled pork had no smoke flavor and certainly no smoke ring.  The brisket was slightly better but still no smoke.  Sauce was needed to provide flavor to all of the meat.  My advice as a Q aficionado...more rub and lots more smoke.  On the plus side the coleslaw and greens were very good.
Great food

Small portions. Mac and cheese had no flavor. It was extremely bland. Ribs where burnt pretty bad. They throw sause over it to mask it. This place is closer to me but I'll drive to caterque or monk's before ever coming back here.
This is my favorite spot in Bethesda. Not that I'm a BBQ expert, but i love the ribs and sides. Great value and outstanding, friendly service. Good selection of craft beers, including local brews.
Best management. ... Awesome experience....They mean business down to the bones of those ribs

Big disappointment.  Meager portion of brisket was uniformly limp and grey with no sign of pink and the au jus they insist on slathering over it ruined what would have been at best a mediocre sandwich.  Pulled pork and pulled chicken were tasteless and bland.  Sauces uninspired, particularly what they call North Carolina BBQ.  The potato salad was nice  - creamy and fresh with bacon bits and no sign of sweetness it but it wasn't enough to save an overpriced and underwhelming meal.  The service is surly and slow.  Red Hot and Blue is still a better bet - cheaper and better.

I came for lunch and enjoyed the BBQ pulled chicken and the coleslaw. The coleslaw was particularly good! It wasn't overly creamy or sweet and had a nice bite to it. I could have eaten a healthy portion of it beyond the small amount that came with the sandwich. I had the mac and cheese as a side and it was also good. I definitely want to come back, perhaps for a BBQ platter for takeaway.
Fabulous BBQ place.  Loved the pulled pork. Very friendly!
The pulled pork sandwich was really good. They opened in January and we just now found it.  We will be back.
